majordomo (0.1.7) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Attach files to a message: `majordomo send --space <id> "text" --attach
    ./file.pdf` uploads a local file and posts it with the message. Repeat
    `--attach` for several files; the message text is optional when a file is
    attached, so a file can go on its own. Works for space, thread, and DM
    targets, through the CLI and the MCP server. The upload uses the send
    scope the token already holds, so no new login is needed.

 -- Weiwu Zhang <a@colourful.land>  Tue, 21 Jul 2026 18:12:34 +1000

majordomo (0.1.6) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Send a private message to a person: `majordomo send --to <email> "text"`
    (or `--to users/<id>`) delivers into your 1:1 Chat DM with them, so
    reaching someone no longer means hunting for a space id. Available
    through the CLI and the MCP server. A person you have no DM with is
    refused by name; majordomo opens no new DMs.
  * `send --help` states what `--to` does rather than what it presumes.

 -- Weiwu Zhang <a@colourful.land>  Mon, 20 Jul 2026 17:45:09 +1000

majordomo (0.1.5) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Add `majordomo send`: post a message to a space, or reply in a thread,
    through the CLI and the MCP server. The privacy sieve refuses blocked
    spaces; a set WORLD_AS_OF refuses every send; `login` now also mints
    the message-create scope (re-run it once before the first send).
  * Rename the direct-API surface to `api`: the pip extra becomes
    `majordomo[api]` and the optional config table `[api]`. The
    `--nocache` read flag keeps its name.

 -- Weiwu Zhang <a@colourful.land>  Thu, 16 Jul 2026 16:21:25 +1000

majordomo (0.1.4) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Add `--live` (cache plus active-space top-up) and rename the API-bypass
    path to `--nocache`.
  * Publish to PyPI (`pip install majordomo`); the Homebrew formula now tracks
    the PyPI sdist.

 -- Weiwu Zhang <a@colourful.land>  Tue, 30 Jun 2026 22:31:35 +1000

